{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1025,"text":"I have a confession to make."},{"time":5433,"text":"As a scientist and engineer,\nI've focused on efficiency for many years."},{"time":13213,"text":"But efficiency can be a cult,"},{"time":17030,"text":"and today I'd like to tell you\nabout a journey"},{"time":20230,"text":"that moved me out of the cult\nand back to a far richer reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28091,"text":"A few years ago, after finishing my Ph.D. \nin London, I moved to Boston."},{"time":33739,"text":"I lived in Boston and worked in Cambridge."},{"time":37381,"text":"I bought a racing bicycle that summer,"},{"time":40576,"text":"and I bicycled every day to work."},{"time":43306,"text":"To find my way, I used my phone."},{"time":45692,"text":"It sent me over Mass. Ave.,\nMassachusetts Avenue,"},{"time":49593,"text":"the shortest route from\nBoston to Cambridge."},{"time":53842,"text":"But after a month"},{"time":55909,"text":"that I was cycling every day\non the car-packed Mass. Ave.,"},{"time":60495,"text":"I took a different route one day."},{"time":63734,"text":"I'm not entirely sure why I took\na different route that day, a detour."},{"time":68795,"text":"I just remember a feeling of surprise;"},{"time":73184,"text":"surprise at finding a street with no cars,"},{"time":77247,"text":"as opposed to the nearby\nMass. Ave. full of cars;"},{"time":81078,"text":"surprise at finding a street \ndraped by leaves and surrounded by trees."},{"time":86395,"text":"But after the feeling \nof surprise, I felt shame."},{"time":91695,"text":"How could I have been so blind?"},{"time":94822,"text":"For an entire month,"},{"time":96728,"text":"I was so trapped in my mobile app"},{"time":99816,"text":"that a journey to work\nbecame one thing only:"},{"time":103322,"text":"the shortest path."},{"time":105783,"text":"In this single journey,\nthere was no thought"},{"time":108876,"text":"of enjoying the road,"},{"time":111507,"text":"no pleasure in connecting with nature,"},{"time":113459,"text":"no possibility of looking\npeople in the eyes."},{"time":117166,"text":"And why?"},{"time":118951,"text":"Because I was saving a minute\nout of my commute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124330,"text":"Now let me ask you: Am I alone here?"},{"time":128399,"text":"How many of you have never used\na mapping app for finding directions?"},{"time":134227,"text":"Most of you, if not all, have."},{"time":136146,"text":"And don't get me wrong -- mapping apps\nare the greatest game-changer"},{"time":141239,"text":"for encouraging people\nto explore the city."},{"time":143816,"text":"You take your phone out\nand you know immediately where to go."},{"time":147993,"text":"However, the app also assumes"},{"time":150904,"text":"there are only a handful\nof directions to the destination."},{"time":156308,"text":"It has the power to make\nthose handful of directions"},{"time":160116,"text":"the definitive direction\nto that destination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165015,"text":"After that experience, I changed."},{"time":167685,"text":"I changed my research\nfrom traditional data-mining"},{"time":171052,"text":"to understanding how people\nexperience the city."},{"time":175324,"text":"I used computer science tools"},{"time":177553,"text":"to replicate social science\nexperiments at scale, at web scale."},{"time":182996,"text":"I became captivated\nby the beauty and genius"},{"time":188118,"text":"of traditional social science experiments"},{"time":191020,"text":"done by Jane Jacobs,\nStanley Milgram, Kevin Lynch."},{"time":195525,"text":"The result of that research\nhas been the creation of new maps,"},{"time":200192,"text":"maps where you don't only find\nthe shortest path, the blue one,"},{"time":205021,"text":"but also the most enjoyable path,"},{"time":208342,"text":"the red one."},{"time":210060,"text":"How was that possible?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":213662,"text":"Einstein once said,"},{"time":215513,"text":"\"Logic will get you from A to B."},{"time":218999,"text":"Imagination will take you everywhere.\""},{"time":221771,"text":"So with a bit of imagination,"},{"time":223689,"text":"we needed to understand"},{"time":225570,"text":"which parts of the city\npeople find beautiful."},{"time":229935,"text":"At the University of Cambridge,\nwith colleagues,"},{"time":232582,"text":"we thought about this simple experiment."},{"time":235740,"text":"If I were to show you\nthese two urban scenes,"},{"time":238898,"text":"and I were to ask you\nwhich one is more beautiful,"},{"time":241684,"text":"which one would you say?"},{"time":246096,"text":"Don't be shy."},{"time":249161,"text":"Who says A? Who says B?"},{"time":252411,"text":"Brilliant."},{"time":254013,"text":"Based on that idea,"},{"time":255987,"text":"we built a crowdsourcing platform,"},{"time":257799,"text":"a web game."},{"time":258913,"text":"Players are shown pairs of urban scenes,"},{"time":261792,"text":"and they're asked to choose which one \nis more beautiful, quiet and happy."},{"time":268154,"text":"Based on thousands of user votes,"},{"time":270104,"text":"then we are able to see\nwhere consensus emerges."},{"time":273308,"text":"We are able to see which\nare the urban scenes"},{"time":276513,"text":"that make people happy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279276,"text":"After that work, I joined Yahoo Labs,"},{"time":282225,"text":"and I teamed up with Luca and Rossano,"},{"time":285104,"text":"and together, we aggregated\nthose winning locations in London"},{"time":288380,"text":"to build a new map of the city,"},{"time":291726,"text":"a cartography weighted for human emotions."},{"time":295993,"text":"On this cartography, you're not only\nable to see and connect"},{"time":299825,"text":"from point A to point B \nthe shortest segments,"},{"time":304677,"text":"but you're also able\nto see the happy segment,"},{"time":307812,"text":"the beautiful path, the quiet path."},{"time":311504,"text":"In tests, participants found the happy,\nthe beautiful, the quiet path"},{"time":316148,"text":"far more enjoyable than the shortest one,"},{"time":319723,"text":"and that just by adding\na few minutes to travel time."},{"time":325528,"text":"Participants also love to attach\nmemories to places."},{"time":329777,"text":"Shared memories --\nthat's where the old BBC building was;"},{"time":334676,"text":"and personal memories --\nthat's where I gave my first kiss."},{"time":339601,"text":"They also recalled how some paths\nsmelled and sounded."},{"time":344034,"text":"So what if we had a mapping tool"},{"time":347261,"text":"that would return\nthe most enjoyable routes"},{"time":349792,"text":"based not only on aesthetics"},{"time":352412,"text":"but also based on smell, sound, \nand memories?"},{"time":355721,"text":"That's where our research\nis going right now."},{"time":359826,"text":"More generally, my research,"},{"time":362028,"text":"what it tries to do is avoid\nthe danger of the single path,"},{"time":366626,"text":"to avoid robbing people of fully\nexperiencing the city in which they live."},{"time":371827,"text":"Walk the path through the park,\nnot through the car park,"},{"time":375565,"text":"and you have an entirely different path."},{"time":377957,"text":"Walk the path full of people you love"},{"time":380905,"text":"and not full of cars,"},{"time":382221,"text":"and you have an entirely different path."},{"time":383939,"text":"It's that simple."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387012,"text":"I would like to end with this thought:"},{"time":389822,"text":"do you remember \"The Truman Show?\""},{"time":391842,"text":"It's a media satire in which a real person"},{"time":394860,"text":"doesn't know he's living\nin a fabricated world."},{"time":398413,"text":"Perhaps we live in a world\nfabricated for efficiency."},{"time":403567,"text":"Look at some of your daily habits,"},{"time":407073,"text":"and as Truman did in the movie,\nescape the fabricated world."},{"time":413226,"text":"Why?"},{"time":414736,"text":"Well, if you think that adventure\nis dangerous, try routine. It's deadly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421416,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423327,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}